@Node DADS8 "Dad's Army > The Battle Of Godfrey's Cottage [#8]"

 @{b}The Battle Of Godfrey's Cottage [#8]@{ub} (1969)
 
 Godfrey's cottage is picked as a machine gun post in the event of an
 invasion. While Mainwaring is in the bank's vault, he doesn't hear the toll
 of the church bells signifying a German invasion. Wilson and Pike head for
 the Novelty Rock Emporium while Jones and Frazer inform Mainwaring and head
 for Godfrey's cottage, unaware where their sergeant has gone.
 
 Eventually Wilson and Pike decide to make for the cottage, which is being
 guarded by the rest of the platoon.
 
 When Jones nips off to the outside toilet, Wilson and Pike mistake him for
 a German and begin shooting. But when Godfrey's sister, oblivious to all
 the pandemonium, waves her tea cloth out of the window, Wilson and Pike
 take it as a sign of surrender and move towards the cottage, only to find
 their supposed enemies are none other than their own men.
 
